The paper discusses the use of a sleep-like phase in artificial neural networks (ANNs) to improve their performance in various tasks. This topic is closely related to the fields of neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
